{
  "texts": [
    "Throughput measures the number of successful TPS, while latency refers to the period needed to validate and execute a transaction.",
    "These properties are decided by the consensus algorithm employed in the Blockchain network.",
    "Suggested SolutionReferences [109,110] a review proposed categorizing available scaling solutions into three tiers: Layer-0 for solutions that improve data transmission standards, Layer-1 for on-chain solutions such as connections, consensus, and data structure, and Layer-2 for off-chain solutions such as off-chain channels, cross-chain protocols, and side-chain approaches.",
    "Additionally, the survey also suggested the use of private or consortium blockchains for IoT and the creation of more scalable consensus algorithms [58].",
    "InteroperabilityRefers to the capability of various Blockchains to interact seamlessly with one another."
  ]
}